  "prompt": "Is GTA IV released on Android?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Grand Theft Auto IV (GTA IV)** has **not been officially released for Android** or any other mobile platforms. Rockstar Games, the developer of the GTA series, has released several titles on mobile devices, including **GTA: San Andreas**, **GTA: Vice City**, and **GTA III**, but GTA IV remains exclusive to consoles and PC.\n\nIf you're interested in playing GTA IV, it's available on the following platforms:\n\n- **PlayStation 3**\n- **Xbox 360**\n- **Microsoft Windows (PC)**\n- **PlayStation 4** and **Xbox One** (through backward compatibility or remastered versions)\n- **PlayStation 5** and **Xbox Series X|S** (via backward compatibility)\n\nFor the latest updates or potential future releases, it's a good idea to regularly check the official Rockstar Games website or their official social media channels.",
